\b WalletApp Architecture Diagrams\b0\par
\par
This document contains key system diagrams for the WalletApp project. Each section includes a short explanation and a Mermaid definition that can be rendered in Mermaid-enabled tools.\par
\par
\b 1) Authentication Diagram\b0\par
Purpose: Shows login/register, JWT issuance, and token-based authorization across gateway and services.\par
\f1
```mermaid\par
flowchart LR\par
  U["User/Admin (Frontend Angular)"] --> G["API Gateway (Ocelot)"]\par
  G --> A["AuthService API"]\par
  A --> DB[(AuthDB: Users, KYC)]\par
  A --> T["TokenService (JWT)"]\par
  T --> A\par
  A --> G\par
  G --> U\par
\par
  U -->|"Authorization: Bearer <JWT>"| G\par
  G -->|"forward token"| W["WalletService / Other Services"]\par
  W -->|"validate JWT claims"| W\par
```\par
\f0
\par
\b 2) HLD (High-Level Design)\b0\par
Purpose: Shows macro architecture of frontend, gateway, microservices, databases, RabbitMQ, and SMTP.\par
\f1
```mermaid\par
flowchart TB\par
  FE["Frontend (Angular)"] --> GW["Gateway (Ocelot)"]\par
\par
  GW --> AUTH["AuthService"]\par
  GW --> WAL["WalletService"]\par
  GW --> ADM["AdminService"]\par
  GW --> REW["RewardService"]\par
  GW --> NOTI["NotificationService"]\par
\par
  AUTH --> AUTHDB[(AuthDB)]\par
  WAL --> WALDB[(WalletDB)]\par
  ADM --> ADMDB[(AdminDB)]\par
  REW --> REWDB[(RewardDB)]\par
  NOTI --> NOTIDB[(NotificationDB)]\par
\par
  AUTH --> MQ[(RabbitMQ)]\par
  WAL --> MQ\par
  ADM --> MQ\par
  REW --> MQ\par
  MQ --> NOTI\par
\par
  NOTI --> SMTP["SMTP (Official App Email)"]\par
```\par
\f0
